{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:job.19",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 19,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 19",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 19 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:2",
      "text": "“How long will you torment me, and break me in pieces with words?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:3",
      "text": "These ten times you have cast reproach upon me; are you not ashamed to wrong me?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:4",
      "text": "And even if it be true that I have erred, my error remains with myself.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:5",
      "text": "If indeed you magnify yourselves against me, and make my humiliation an argument against me,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:6",
      "text": "know then that God has put me in the wrong, and closed his net about me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:7",
      "text": "Behold, I cry out, ‘Violence!’ but I am not answered; I call aloud, but there is no justice.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:8",
      "text": "He has walled up my way, so that I cannot pass, and he has set darkness upon my paths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:9",
      "text": "He has stripped from me my glory, and taken the crown from my head.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:10",
      "text": "He breaks me down on every side, and I am gone, and my hope has he pulled up like a tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:11",
      "text": "He has kindled his wrath against me, and counts me as his adversary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:12",
      "text": "His troops come on together; they have cast up siegeworks against me, and encamp round about my tent.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:13",
      "text": "“He has put my brethren far from me, and my acquaintances are wholly estranged from me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:14",
      "text": "My kinsfolk and my close friends have failed me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:15",
      "text": "the guests in my house have forgotten me; my maidservants count me as a stranger; I have become an alien in their eyes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:16",
      "text": "I call to my servant, but he gives me no answer; I must beseech him with my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:17",
      "text": "I am repulsive to my wife, loathsome to the sons of my own mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:18",
      "text": "Even young children despise me; when I rise they talk against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:19",
      "text": "All my intimate friends abhor me, and those whom I loved have turned against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:20",
      "text": "My bones cleave to my skin and to my flesh, and I have escaped by the skin of my teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:21",
      "text": "Have pity on me, have pity on me, O you my friends, for the hand of God has touched me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:22",
      "text": "Why do you, like God, pursue me? Why are you not satisfied with my flesh?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:23",
      "text": "“Oh that my words were written! Oh that they were inscribed in a book!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:24",
      "text": "Oh that with an iron pen and lead they were graven in the rock for ever!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:25",
      "text": "For I know that my Redeemer lives, and at last he will stand upon the earth;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:26",
      "text": "and after my skin has been thus destroyed, then from my flesh I shall see God,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:27",
      "text": "whom I shall see on my side, and my eyes shall behold, and not another. My heart faints within me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.28",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:28",
      "text": "If you say, ‘How we will pursue him!’ and, ‘The root of the matter is found in him’;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:job.19.29",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 19,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 19:29",
      "text": "be afraid of the sword, for wrath brings the punishment of the sword, that you may know there is a judgment.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
